# Source: redhat-trusted-profile-analyzer/templates/init/guac/010-ConfigMap.yaml
kind: ConfigMap
apiVersion: v1
metadata:
  name: init-guac-db
  labels:
    app.kubernetes.io/name: init-guac-db
    app.kubernetes.io/component: guac
    app.kubernetes.io/instance: redhat-trusted-profile-analyzer
    app.kubernetes.io/version: "1.1.1"
    app.kubernetes.io/part-of: "trusted-profile-analyzer"
    
  annotations:
    
    
    argocd.argoproj.io/hook: Sync
    argocd.argoproj.io/hook-delete-policy: BeforeHookCreation
    argocd.argoproj.io/sync-wave: "0"
    helm.sh/hook-weight: "5"
    helm.sh/hook: "pre-install,pre-upgrade"
    helm.sh/hook-delete-policy: before-hook-creation

data:
  init.sql: |
    -- ensure we have the database
    SELECT 'CREATE DATABASE ' || :'db_name'
    WHERE NOT EXISTS (SELECT FROM pg_database WHERE datname = :'db_name')\gexec
    
    -- create the user (if it doesn't exist)
    CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION add_user_if_not_exists(username NAME) RETURNS integer
        AS $$
    BEGIN
        IF NOT EXISTS (SELECT FROM pg_roles
            WHERE rolname = username) THEN

            EXECUTE FORMAT('CREATE ROLE "%I" LOGIN', username);

        END IF;
        RETURN NULL;
    END;
    $$ language plpgsql;

    SELECT add_user_if_not_exists(:'db_user');

    -- now set the password
    ALTER USER :db_user WITH PASSWORD :'db_password';

    -- grant permission to connect
    GRANT CONNECT ON DATABASE :db_name TO :db_user;
    
    -- grant permissions on database
    \connect :db_name
    
    GRANT USAGE ON SCHEMA public TO :db_user;
    
    -- grant on existing tables
    GRANT SELECT, INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE ON ALL TABLES IN SCHEMA public TO :db_user;
    
    -- grant on future tables
    ALTER DEFAULT PRIVILEGES
        IN SCHEMA public
        GRANT SELECT, INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE ON TABLES TO :db_user;

kind: Job

metadata:
  name: init-guac-db

    app.kubernetes.io/part-of: "trusted-profile-analyzer"
    

  annotations:

    helm.sh/hook-weight: "5"
    helm.sh/hook: "pre-install,pre-upgrade"
    helm.sh/hook-delete-policy: before-hook-creation

spec:
  backoffLimit: 1000
  completions: 1
  parallelism: 1
  ttlSecondsAfterFinished: 600

  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
            app.kubernetes.io/name: init-guac-db
            app.kubernetes.io/component: guac
            app.kubernetes.io/instance: redhat-trusted-profile-analyzer

    spec:

      restartPolicy: OnFailure
      

      volumes:
        - name: init-data
          configMap:
            name: init-guac-db
        

      containers:
        - name: setup
          
          image: registry.redhat.io/rhtpa/rhtpa-trustification-service-rhel9@sha256:60f676f8c7611d08827f5e1cad332d7ebc5d6660392618c29d1966c1825cff5b
          imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent
      

          env:
            # connect using the `initDatabase` settings
            
            - name: PGHOST
              valueFrom:
                secretKeyRef:
                  key: POSTGRES_HOST
                  name: keycloak-db-secret
            - name: PGPORT
              value: "5432"
            - name: PGDATABASE
              valueFrom:
                secretKeyRef:
                  key: POSTGRES_DATABASE
                  name: keycloak-db-secret
            - name: PGUSER
              value: "postgres"
            - name: PGPASSWORD
              value: "postgres"
            
            
            - name: PGSSLMODE
              value: disable

            # create a user with the `database` settings
            - name: DB_NAME
              value: "guac"
            - name: DB_USERNAME
              value: "guac"
            - name: DB_PASSWORD
              value: "guac1234"

          volumeMounts:
            - mountPath: /etc/init-data
              name: init-data
            

          command:
            - psql
            - -v
            - ON_ERROR_STOP=1
            - -v
            - db_name=$(DB_NAME)
            - -v
            - db_user=$(DB_USERNAME)
            - -v
            - db_password=$(DB_PASSWORD)
            - -f
            - /etc/init-data/init.sql

apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: spog-ui-config
  labels:
    app.kubernetes.io/name: spog-ui-config
    app.kubernetes.io/component: branding
    app.kubernetes.io/instance: redhat-trusted-profile-analyzer

    app.kubernetes.io/part-of: "trusted-profile-analyzer"
    
data:
  spog-ui.yaml: |-
    $schema: "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/trustification/trustification/main/spog/model/schema/config.json"
    
    global:
      documentationUrl: https://access.redhat.com/documentation/en-us/red_hat_trusted_profile_analyzer/1
      supportUrl: https://issues.redhat.com/browse/TC
      productName: Red Hat Trusted Profile Analyzer
      brandImageSrc: branding/logo.svg
      supportCaseUrl: https://issues.redhat.com/projects/TC/issues/
      supportCaseLabel: "Support (Jira)"
      aboutBackgroundSrc: ""
      aboutBrandImageSrc: branding/about-logo.svg
      showGithubLink: false
    
    features:
      dedicatedSearch: false
      additionalPackageInformation: false
      showSource: false
      scanner: false
      uploader: true
      showReport: true
      extendSection: true
    
    bombastic:
    
      filters:
        categories:
    
          - label: Products
            options:
    
              - type: check
                label: UBI 7
                id: ubi7
                terms:
                  - '"pkg:oci/ubi7"'
    
              - type: check
                label: UBI 8
                id: ubi8
                terms:
                  - '"pkg:oci/ubi8"'
    
              - type: check
                label: UBI 9
                id: ubi9
                terms:
                  - '"pkg:oci/ubi9"'
    
              - type: divider
    
              - type: check
                label: Red Hat Enterprise Linux 7
                id: rhel7
                terms:
                  - '"cpe:/o:redhat:enterprise_linux:7"'
                  - '"cpe:/o:redhat:rhel_aus:7"'
    
              - type: check
                label: Red Hat Enterprise Linux 8
                id: rhel8
                terms:
                  - '"cpe:/o:redhat:enterprise_linux:8"'
                  - '"cpe:/o:redhat:rhel_e4s:8.1"'
    
              - type: check
                label: Red Hat Enterprise Linux 9
                id: rhel9
                terms:
                  - '"cpe:/o:redhat:enterprise_linux:9"'
    
              - type: divider
    
              - type: check
                label: Ansible
                id: ansible
                terms:
                  - '"cpe:/a:redhat:ansible_automation_platform"'
    
              - type: check
                label: AMQ
                id: amq
                terms:
                  - '"cpe:/a:redhat:amq" OR "amq-"'
    
              - type: check
                label: Quarkus
                id: quarkus
                terms:
                  - '"quarkus"'
    
          - label: Type
            options:
              - type: check
                label: Container
                id: is_container
                terms:
                  - 'type:oci'
    
              - type: check
                label: Product
                id: is_product
                terms:
                  - 'NOT type:oci'
    
          - label: Suppliers
            options:
              - type: check
                label: Red Hat
                id: supplier_redhat
                terms:
                  - 'supplier:"Organization: Red Hat"'
    
          - label: Created on
            options:
              - type: select
                group: created-on
                default: any
                options:
                  - id: last-week
                    label: Last 7 days
                    script: |
                      const end = new Date();
                      const start = new Date(end.getTime() - (7 * 24 * 60 * 60 * 1000));
                      [
                        "created:" + 
                        start.toLocaleString("default", { year: "numeric" }) + "-" +
                        start.toLocaleString("default", { month: "2-digit" }) + "-" +
                        start.toLocaleString("default", { day: "2-digit" }) + ".." +
                        end.toLocaleString("default", { year: "numeric" }) + "-" +
                        end.toLocaleString("default", { month: "2-digit" }) + "-" +
                        end.toLocaleString("default", { day: "2-digit" })
                      ];
                  - id: last-month
                    label: Last 30 days
                    script: |
                      const end = new Date();
                      const start = new Date(end.getTime() - (30 * 24 * 60 * 60 * 1000));
                      [
                        "created:" + 
                        start.toLocaleString("default", { year: "numeric" }) + "-" +
                        start.toLocaleString("default", { month: "2-digit" }) + "-" +
                        start.toLocaleString("default", { day: "2-digit" }) + ".." +
                        end.toLocaleString("default", { year: "numeric" }) + "-" +
                        end.toLocaleString("default", { month: "2-digit" }) + "-" +
                        end.toLocaleString("default", { day: "2-digit" })
                      ];
                  - id: this-year
                    label: This year
                    script: |
                      const date = new Date();
                      const start = new Date(date.getFullYear(), 0, 1);
                      const end = new Date(date.getFullYear()+1, 0, 1);
                      [
                        "created:" + 
                        start.toLocaleString("default", { year: "numeric" }) + "-" +
                        start.toLocaleString("default", { month: "2-digit" }) + "-" +
                        start.toLocaleString("default", { day: "2-digit" }) + ".." +
                        end.toLocaleString("default", { year: "numeric" }) + "-" +
                        end.toLocaleString("default", { month: "2-digit" }) + "-" +
                        end.toLocaleString("default", { day: "2-digit" })
                      ];
                  - id: "2023"
                    label: "2023"
                    terms:
                      - 'created:2023-01-01..2024-01-01'
                  - id: "2022"
                    label: "2022"
                    terms:
                      - 'created:2022-01-01..2023-01-01'
                  - id: "any"
                    label: "Any time"
    
    vexination:
    
      filters:
        categories:
          - label: Severity
            options:
              - type: check
                id: low
                label: |
                  <span class="tc-c-severity">
                      <span class="tc-c-severity__icon"> <span class="tc-m-severity-low"> <i class="fa fa-shield-halved"></i> </span></span>
                      <span class="tc-c-severity__text"> Low </span>
                  </span>
                terms:
                  - "severity:Low"
    
              - type: check
                id: moderate
                label: |
                  <span class="tc-c-severity">
                      <span class="tc-c-severity__icon"> <span class="tc-m-severity-moderate"> <i class="fa fa-shield-halved"></i> </span></span>
                      <span class="tc-c-severity__text"> Moderate </span>

          imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent
          

          command: [ "/bin/sh" ]
          args:
            - -ec
            - |
              TC_PGOPTIONS="?"
              TC_PGOPTIONS="${TC_PGOPTIONS}sslmode=${TC_PGSSLMODE}&"
              exec /opt/guac/guacmigrate "--db-address" "postgres://${TC_PGUSER}:${TC_PGPASSWORD}@${TC_PGHOST}:${TC_PGPORT}/${TC_PGDATABASE}${TC_PGOPTIONS}" "--db-driver" "postgres" "--db-debug" "true"

            - name: TC_PGDATABASE
              value: "guac"
            - name: TC_PGUSER
              value: "postgres"
            - name: TC_PGPASSWORD
              value: "postgres"
            
            
            - name: TC_PGSSLMODE
              value: disable

          volumeMounts:
            

      containers:
        - name: service
          
          image: registry.redhat.io/rhtpa/rhtpa-guac-rhel9@sha256:1472d5acb56cb72d49cd0d25186e6a02af53cd14c84c1a22357d115958921e52
          imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent
          

          command: ["/bin/sh"]

          # not sure why --db-migrate=false has to be a single argument, but it won't work otherwise
          args:
            - -ec
            - |
              TC_PGOPTIONS="?"
              TC_PGOPTIONS="${TC_PGOPTIONS}sslmode=${TC_PGSSLMODE}&"
              exec /opt/guac/guacgql "--gql-backend" "ent" "--db-address" "postgres://${TC_PGUSER}:${TC_PGPASSWORD}@${TC_PGHOST}:${TC_PGPORT}/${TC_PGDATABASE}${TC_PGOPTIONS}" "--db-driver" "postgres" "--db-migrate=false"

            - name: TC_PGHOST
              value: "keycloak-postgresql"
            - name: TC_PGPORT
              value: "5432"
            - name: TC_PGDATABASE
              value: "guac"
            - name: TC_PGUSER
              value: "guac"
            - name: TC_PGPASSWORD
              value: "guac1234"
            
            
            - name: TC_PGSSLMODE
              value: disable
            
            - name: GUAC_GQL_TLS_CERT_FILE
              value: /etc/tls/tls.crt
            - name: GUAC_GQL_TLS_KEY_FILE
              value: /etc/tls/tls.key
            - name: GUAC_PROMETHEUS_ADDR
              value: "9010"

          volumeMounts:
            
            - mountPath: /etc/tls
              name: tls
              readOnly: true
            
            

          readinessProbe:

              port: 8080
              scheme: HTTPS

apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: CronJob
metadata:
  name: v11y-walker
  labels:
    app.kubernetes.io/name: v11y-walker
    app.kubernetes.io/component: v11y
    app.kubernetes.io/instance: redhat-trusted-profile-analyzer
    app.kubernetes.io/version: "1.1.1"
    app.kubernetes.io/managed-by: Helm
    app.kubernetes.io/part-of: "trusted-profile-analyzer"
    

spec:
  schedule: "0 1 * * *"
  suspend: false
  concurrencyPolicy: Forbid
  jobTemplate:
    spec:
      template:
        metadata:
          labels:
            app.kubernetes.io/name: v11y-walker
            app.kubernetes.io/component: v11y
            app.kubernetes.io/instance: redhat-trusted-profile-analyzer

        spec:
          

          restartPolicy: Never
          volumes:
            - name: cvelist
              persistentVolumeClaim:
                claimName: v11y-walker
            

          initContainers:
            - name: git-fetch
              
              image: registry.redhat.io/rhtpa/rhtpa-trustification-service-rhel9@sha256:60f676f8c7611d08827f5e1cad332d7ebc5d6660392618c29d1966c1825cff5b
              imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent
              

              volumeMounts:
                - mountPath: /git
                  name: cvelist

              command: ["/bin/sh"]
              workingDir: /git
              args:
                - "-ec"
                - |
                  if test -d cvelistV5; then
                    cd cvelistV5
                    git pull
                  else
                    git clone https://github.com/CVEProject/cvelistV5
                  fi

          containers:
            - name: walker
              
              image: registry.redhat.io/rhtpa/rhtpa-trustification-service-rhel9@sha256:60f676f8c7611d08827f5e1cad332d7ebc5d6660392618c29d1966c1825cff5b
              imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent
              
              livenessProbe:
                initialDelaySeconds: 2
                httpGet:
                  path: /health/live
                  port: 9010
              
              readinessProbe:
                initialDelaySeconds: 2
                httpGet:
                  path: /health/ready
                  port: 9010
          

              volumeMounts:
                - mountPath: /mnt
                  name: cvelist
                

              command: ["/trust"]
              args:
                - "v11y"
                - "walker"
                - "--source"
                - "/mnt/cvelistV5"

              
                - "--delta-file"
                - "/mnt/last-delta"
              

              env:
                
                - name: RUST_LOG
                  value: "info"
                
                - name: INFRASTRUCTURE_ENABLED
                  value: "true"
                - name: INFRASTRUCTURE_BIND
                  value: "[::]:9010"
                - name: STORAGE_ACCESS_KEY
                  valueFrom:
                    secretKeyRef:
                      key: root-user
                      name: infrastructure-minio
                
                - name: STORAGE_SECRET_KEY
                  valueFrom:
                    secretKeyRef:
                      key: root-password
                      name: infrastructure-minio
                
                
                - name: STORAGE_ENDPOINT
                  value: "http://infrastructure-minio:9000"
                - name: STORAGE_REGION
                  value: "eu-west-1" # just a dummy value
                
                
                - name: STORAGE_BUCKET
                  value: "v11y-default"

              ports:
                
                - containerPort: 9010
                  protocol: TCP
                  name: infra
